WHEREAS, in 1956, ground was broken on the same property for St. Dominic School, a
Catholic elementary school for boys operated by the Dominican Sisters in conjunction with St.
Agnes Academy; and
WHEREAS, over the years, numerous improvements and expansions have enhanced
the campus, including the addition of Siena Hall, the Veritas Research Center and Distance
Learning Center, the Davis Early Childhood Center, and the Math and Science Center; and
WHEREAS, students of St. Agnes Academy have excelled in athletics, winning
numerous regional and state titles in golf, soccer, bowling, track, and tennis, and the school was
awarded the Best of the Preps Award for the Female Division in 2011 and 2012; and
WHEREAS, guided by the Dominican Pillars of study, prayer, community, and service,
students collectively volunteer more than 18,000 hours of service annually, embodying the spirit
of faith and commitment to truth that have defined St. Agnes Academy for generations; and
WHEREAS, today, St. Agnes Academy stands as the oldest continuously operating
school in Memphis and the oldest Dominican school in the country, and it is fitting that we honor
this venerable institution on its 175th anniversary; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we recognize and honor St. Agnes Academy on the occasion of its 175th
anniversary, extending to this esteemed institution our best wishes for continued success in the
years to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
